   <text>
      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Mauritius ¶ 5th Jany 1865 ¶ My Dear Sir William ¶  ¶ [Discusses issues to do with the botany of Mauritius and the management of the Gardens] ¶ …...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M65.01.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Henry Barkly to William Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' correspondence, vol 60, f 39.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Mauritius</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5th Jany 1865</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My Dear Sir William</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Discusses issues to do with the botany of Mauritius and the management of the Gardens]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">…</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I suppose our friend Dr Mueller has sent you his little books on the Chatham Island Plants<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.02.</p>
               </note> &amp; on Australian Mosses.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.03.</p>
               </note> He seems still very much dispirited and put out, and complaining that Mr Bentham writes to him as if he were the veriest tyro in the Science. There is probably no small amount of morbid sensitiveness in all this, but if you had the opportunity of quietly giving a hint to the learned President of the Linnean Society,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Bentham.</p>
               </note> it might smooth matters. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mueller is fond of highsounding complimentary phrases and ponderous courtesy like most Germans, but he is a good creature at heart and I am sorry to find him so thoroughly dissatisfied with his share of the Flora of Australia.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863–78).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">…</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[Lady Barkly is looking forward to receiving Hooker’s work on Ferns.]</p>
         </div>
      </body>
